<p><b>What is the message of Doubt: A Parable?</b> In this fictional narrative dramatized in the Pulitzer- and Tony Award-winning play, "Doubt: A Parable," themes of sexual misconduct, faith, gossip and suspicion create an intense look at situations that apply not only in the church setting, but in other parts of society as well.</p>
<p><b>What is the summary of Doubt: A Parable?</b> Set against the backdrop of a 1960s America in the midst of political and social change, a progressive young priest's conduct comes under question by Sister Aloysius Beauvier, the school principal whose beliefs are deeply rooted in tradition.</p>
